                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="a1">
                                    <locus from="2r" to="3r"/>
                                    <desc type="GuestText">Excerpt from the <title ref="LIT1099Anapho"/>, written in the main hand. 
                                        The note reproduces the same text found on <locus from="61r" to="62v"/> and corresponds to 
                                        <bibl><ptr target="bm:Petrus1548Test"/><citedRange unit="page">172va, last line-172vb, l. 12</citedRange></bibl>.
                                        Liturgical directives in abbreviation and elements of the punctuation signs are rubricated.
                                    </desc>  
                                    <q xml:lang="gez"><seg part="I">የ፡ ትዜንዉ። <abbr><hi rend="rubric">ይካ፡</hi></abbr> ኦእግዚኦ፡ በከመ፡ አሜሃ፡ ዘንተ፡ ኅብስተ፡ ባርክ። ወፈትት፡ 
                                        ወሀብ፡ እግዚኦ፡ በከመ፡ አሜሃ፡ ዘንተ፡ ጽዋዓ፡ ዕቀብ። ወቀድስ፡ ወመጡ።</seg></q>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez"><seg part="F">በከመ፡ ሕገ፡ ላዕክ፡ አ<add place="interlinear">ብ</add>ጽሖ፡ ካ<add place="interlinear">ዕ</add>በ፡ ዘየአቤ፡ ማዕረግ፡ 
                                        ሴመተ፡ ካህነት። ወረሰዮ፡ ምሉዓ።</seg></q>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e1">
                                    <desc>A white sticker is glued on the inner side of the front board. The name of <persName ref="PRS5782JuelJen"/> is printed on it
                                        (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ቤንት፡ ዩውል፡ የንሰን።</foreign>) and the signature "MS. Aeth. f. 32" is written in pencil.
                                    </desc>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="e2">
                                    <desc>Some writings have been added in pencil on <locus target="#1r"/> by the hand of <persName ref="PRS5782JuelJen"/>. On the upper margin is written
                                        an amount of money which presumably indicates the price of sale of the manuscript <q xml:lang="en">"£ 120"</q>; below are found
                                        information on the dating and the decorations <q xml:lang="en">"C 18 - 2 miniatures"</q>, as well as the signature of the book <q xml:lang="en">"Ms Aeth. J-J 39"</q>.
                                        Furthermore, the title of the book in English <q xml:lang="en">"Praise for the Holy Communion of Our Mother Mary written 
                                            <supplied reason="omitted">by</supplied> Aba Hariyaqos of Bhansa"</q> is written on the lower margin of <locus target="#1r"/>.
                                    </desc>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="e3">
                                    <desc>
                                        Corrections are infrequent. They mostly consist of interlineal additions (e.g. <locus target="#17r #21v #65v"/>) and corrections through dashes above and below 
                                        the letters (e.g. <locus target="#15r #43v #75r"/>).
                                    </desc>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="e4">
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1v"/>
                                    <locus from="82v" to="84r"/>
                                    <desc>Scribbles and pen trials in blue or violet ink.</desc> 
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="e5">
                                    <locus target="#3v"/> 
                                    <locus from="86r" to="86v"/>
                                    <desc>Crude drawings of human figures in red ink or blue pencil.</desc> 
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="e6">
                                    <locus from="81v" to="82r"/>
                                    <desc>Several names of individuals have been added in blue pencil or violet ink in a very inaccurate handwriting.
                                        The names of <persName ref="PRS13885GabraHe"/> (spelled once as Gabra Ḥaywat), <persName ref="PRS13886GabraIy"/> (spelled once as Gabra ʾƎyasus), 
                                        <persName ref="PRS13887WaldaGa"/> (spelled as Walda Garʾel), and <persName ref="PRS13888WalattaGa"/> are still legible.</desc> 
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </additions>
                    
